         <abstract>
            <p>This paper is concerned with a centered finite-difference approximation to the nonselfadjoint Sturm-Liouville eigenvalue problem \begin{align*}L\lbrack u \rbrack &amp;= -\lbrack a(x)u_x \rbrack_x - b(x)u_x + c(x)u = \lambda u,\quad 0 &lt; x &lt; 1,\\ u(0) &amp;= u(1) = 0.\end{align*} It is shown that the eigenvectors $W_p$ of the $M \times M$-matrix ($\Delta x = 1/(M + 1)$ mesh size), which approximates $L$, are bounded in the maximum norm independent of $M$ if they are normalized so that $|W_p|_2 = 1$.</p>
         </abstract>
